  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/vad-cou2-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-board",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels at MRL 5. The operating envelope is explicitly bounded (flow rate 1–7 L/min, rotational speed 2000–5000 RPM, hematocrit 35–45 %, temperature 36–38 °C, inlet pressure 0–20 mmHg) and validation experiments cover all declared boundary points. Monte Carlo UQ confirms NIH predictions within 95 % PI at all operating points. Discretization error (GCI < 2.1 % for NIH) and solver convergence are well-controlled. Model form selection is justified by published benchmarks. Independent review confirmed no use errors. The structured operating envelope and applicability constraint ensure the model is not applied outside its validated domain. The credibility evidence is sufficient to support regulatory submission for this Class III VAD device.",
